The Habit Burger Grill in Gaithersburg serves some of my favorite burgers. I stopped by on my way home from work knowing I could count on a delicious meal. Tonight, a Chat cheeseburger with bacon, accompanied by their seasonal Garlic fries. Perfect! The burger was cooked just right and all the toppings were crisp and the bun had just the slightest crunch. The fries were not only delicious, they also looked great served with garlic sauce for perfect seasoning. The staff have always been friendly with good service.  I highly recommend stopping in!

I ordered a grilled chicken sandwich plain, a side of french fries, and a coffee flavored milkshake.  As far as I could tell, everything on the menu was being sold a la carte.  If I am wrong and their menu isn't just a la carte, then the portion of the menu that is dedicated to combo deals/ or full meal specials, must've invisible because I couldnt find it.  As a matter of fact,  I almost left when I saw the prices but I was so hungry and didn't want to go elsewhere and have to wait their too so I decided to stick to the plan and try their food.  The food was definitely pricey for fast food, my three items costed $13 in total, and left me wanting. The food tasted pretty darn good though, I really liked it a lot.  The milkshake, however, was totally whack, it tasted like generic vanilla ice cream (not coffee) and was just subpar at best.  I don't think that milkshakes are the Habits' specialty, but this had little impact on my rating and final review just because it's a damn milkshake and I dont think it should have the power to make or break their business's success.  Sadly, despite my overall positive review and the mostly delicious menu served at "The Habit," I probably won't visit very often anyways, despite the mostly great flavor.  This is for 2 reasons, the first being that the portions are way too small. Now, I know what you're thinking, I got a PLAIN chicken sandwich- how huge could I be expecting the sandwich to be?  Well, let me put it like this- McDonalds plain chicken sandwich makes the Habit's plain chicken sandwich look like a slider.  The Habit tastes better but I won't still be hungry after eating a McDonald's chicken sandwich, and it's like half the price.  Which brings me to my next problem, the price.  The food is great, but it's too little food for too much money, and this is the sole reason that I won't be back.  I gave a good rating because the food IS good, but I wouldn't consider this as an affordable, fast food option.
